TITLE: NY lieutenant governor the focus of federal campaign fraud probe: Report
SUMMARY: Federal investigators have reportedly issued subpoenas to the New York Senate and former campaign advisers of New York Lt. Gov. Brian Benjamin, trying to determine whether he had a hand in funneling fraudulent donations to his failed 2021 campaign.

TITLE: Zelenskyy: West needs more courage in helping Ukraine fight
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy accused the West of cowardice as his country fights to stave off Russia’s invading troops, making an exasperated plea for fighter jets and tanks to sustain a defense as the war ground into a battle of attrition.

TITLE: Sen. Booker on resolution of Russia-Ukraine conflict: 'I don't see how this ends well' for Putin
SUMMARY: Sen. Cory Booker does not know exactly how the war between Russia and Ukraine will end, but he is confident that whatever the resolution will be is bad news for Russian President Vladimir Putin.

TITLE: Kyiv Mayor Klitschko: Ukraine soldiers 'show big will to win this fight'
SUMMARY: Kyiv Mayor Vitali Klitschko detailed the latest situation on the ground in the capital of Ukraine during an exclusive interview on Sunday, saying that soldiers in the country are showing a “big will” to win the war.

TITLE: France's Macron warns against escalation after Biden says Putin 'cannot remain in power'
SUMMARY: French President Macron said he wouldn't use the same wording as President Biden to describe Putin -- a "butcher" who "cannot remain in power" -- saying his goal was a cease-fire and the withdrawal of Russian troops from Ukraine.

TITLE: Biden approval ratings plummet amid war and inflation fears in new public opinion poll
SUMMARY: President Biden’s job approval rating declined to 40%, the lowest level of his presidency, and Republicans enjoy a 2-point lead over Democrats ahead of the midterms, a new NBC News poll shows.

TITLE: US ambassador to NATO cleans up Biden’s remarks, says ‘US does not have a policy of regime change in Russia’
SUMMARY: U.S. Ambassador to NATO Julianne Smith said on "Fox News Sunday" that the U.S. does not have a policy of regime change towards Russia, clarifying earlier remarks by President Biden in Warsaw, Poland.

TITLE: Trump’s grip on the GOP remains firm, but is the former president stretching himself too thin?
SUMMARY: Donald Trump remains the most influential politician in the GOP, but has the former president over-extended himself by making too many endorsements in the 2022 elections?

TITLE: House GOP pushes Wray for transparency on FBI misconduct in probing politicians, religious groups, journalists
SUMMARY: Rep. Andy Biggs, R-Ariz., contends Democrats have a stake in digging for more details about the FBI breaking its own rules to probe elected officials, political candidates, religious organizations and the news media

TITLE: Stefanik says becoming a mother made her 'more effective leader,' says moms in Congress 'on a mission'
SUMMARY: EXCLUSIVE: PONTE VEDRA, FLA.— House Republican Caucus Chair Elise Stefanik said becoming a mother has made her “a more effective leader” and told Fox News that she and other mothers in Congress are “moms on a mission” to strengthen the country for the next generation.

TITLE: US special ops veterans, medical professionals training Ukrainian soldiers, civilians in combat care
SUMMARY: A group of American Special Operations veterans and medical professionals are on the ground in Ukraine, training Ukrainian forces, doctors and civilians in how to address a range of medicine and surgery issues, from treating front-line combat injuries to advanced trauma surgery interventions.

TITLE: Trump returns to Georgia confronting test of his grip on GOP
SUMMARY: In Donald Trump's push to fundamentally reshape the Republican Party, few places are a higher priority than Georgia.

TITLE: Today's political cartoon: War on capitalism
Trump: 'How on earth' can Judge Jackson say what the Constitution is if she can't say what a woman is
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump blasted Biden Supreme Court nominee Ketanji Brown Jackson over her inability to provide the definition of a woman during her confirmation hearing this week.

TITLE: Former President Donald Trump holds 'Save America' rally in Georgia
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump is speaking at a rally in Commerce, Georgia on Saturday night.

TITLE: Nebraska Rep. Jeff Fortenberry to resign from Congress after lying to FBI
SUMMARY: Rep. Jeff Fortenberry, R-Neb., announced Saturday that he will resign from Congress after he was convicted by a California jury for lying to authorities about an illegal campaign donation from a foreign national.

TITLE: Putin heard 'loud and clear' call for regime change after Biden said he 'cannot remain in power': expert
SUMMARY: President Biden's speech Saturday in Poland affirmed to Russian President Vladimir Putin what he already long suspected – the U.S. wants him out of power, a Russia expert told Fox News Digital.

TITLE: White House walks back multiple Biden remarks during Europe trip on Putin, chemical weapons, troops
SUMMARY: The White House has been forced to walk back or clarify multiple remarks made by President Biden during his trip to Europe, including on whether he was calling for regime change in Russia.

TITLE: Biden says Putin ‘cannot remain in power’ as he assures Ukraine: ‘We stand with you’
SUMMARY: President Biden on Saturday said that Russian President Vladimir Putin "cannot remain in power," as he declared the Russian invasion of Ukraine a "strategic failure" while pledging continued support for the embattled Ukrainian people.

TITLE: Biden says 'thousands of people a day' crossing US border as officials brace for new migrant surge
SUMMARY: President Biden on Saturday told Polish officials the U.S. has “thousands of people a day” trying to cross the U.S. southern border just as officials are bracing for a massive migrant surge in the months ahead and are already seeing signs of increased numbers.
